description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit highly motivated individuals to join our Respiratory Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides safe and high standards of specialist care to all patients throughout their stay on the respiratory ward as well as assisting in the discharge process, liaising with family members and external agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will assist with patient hygiene needs, toileting, nutritional intake, assisting patients with their mobility and physical comfort and monitoring and recording vital signs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must demonstrate a compassionate and caring attitude towards their patients and be able to deliver high standards of care. It is essential to possess good communication and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are dedicated to the on going development of our staff, you will undertake trust induction; healthcare specific training and ward based training alongside our clinical nurse educator as well as have other opportunities to undertake training relevant to our specialist area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**Please note that it is a requirement to hold your Numeracy and Literacy for this position. If you do not hold your Literacy qualification, you will be given the opportunity to complete our in house assessment**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:  Leanne Barkess-Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Ward 21RE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manager:  Email addressleanne.barkess@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:  01743 261000 extension 3932&lt;/p&gt;
